other_tests.findings: Marked circumferential enlargement of the subcutaneous tissue due to fatty hypertrophy. Fat lobules surrounded by thick fibrous septa and thickening of the overlying dermis.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Initial diagnosis of lymphedema progressed to lipedema over a period of 7 years; findings suggest superimposed lymphatic involvement.

other_tests.findings: Massive bilateral lower extremity enlargement with minimal pitting, firm subcutaneous nodules, normal skin appearance, moderate edema of the dorsal foot, and a positive result for Stemmer's sign.
